<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="320" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[813,1452,865,920]" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,956,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">Etymology. –</emphasis>
The name of this species refers to the 3 spines on the male left cercus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[813,1452,961,1240]" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1166,961,985]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">Phylogenetic relationships. –</emphasis>
The relationships of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinicercus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">S. spinicercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear beyond inclusion within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graminum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">S. graminum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. The structure of the female terminalia and the upper lobe of the left surstylus may suggest closer relationships with the 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fallen)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" box="[1133,1367,1089,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graminum">
<emphasis box="[1133,1273,1089,1112]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">S. graminum</emphasis>
(Fàllen)
</taxonomicName>
and its allies, though the structure of the right surstylus resembles that in 
<taxonomicName authority="Collin." authorityName="Collin." box="[886,1071,1153,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubilus">
<emphasis box="[886,991,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">S. nubilus</emphasis>
Collin.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2004" box="[1076,1223,1153,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinicercus">
<emphasis box="[1076,1223,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">S. spinicercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of this group which has the gland-like structures on the male abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="320" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[813,1452,1281,1400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1256,1281,1305]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">Distribution and seasonal occurrence. –</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[1264,1362,1281,1304]" name="Thailand" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. Known from two areas: 
<collectingRegion box="[985,1034,1313,1336]" country="Thailand" name="Loei" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">Loei</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1085,1204,1313,1336]" country="Thailand" name="Chanthaburi" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">Chantaburi</collectingRegion>
provinces. Records are almost from the whole year, except July, August, and most part of September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
